text: Duck Creek is a stream in Brown and Outagamie counties, Wisconsin, in the United States. Duck Creek was named for the many ducks seen along its banks by trappers. In the Menominee language, it is known as Sēqsepaketaheqkoneh, an archaic name meaning "duck landing place". ==See also== *List of rivers of Wisconsin ==References== Category:Rivers of Brown County, Wisconsin Category:Bodies of water of Outagamie County, Wisconsin Category:Rivers of Wisconsin
